{"id":581163089,"lang":"java","time":"1 month, 1 week","timestamp":1635889102,"status_display":"Accepted","runtime":"2 ms","url":"/submissions/detail/581163089/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Add Two Numbers II","memory":"39.3 MB","code":"/**\n * Definition for singly-linked list.\n * public class ListNode {\n *     int val;\n *     ListNode next;\n *     ListNode() {}\n *     ListNode(int val) { this.val = val; }\n *     ListNode(int val, ListNode next) { this.val = val; this.next = next; }\n * }\n */\nclass Solution {\n    \n    public ListNode reverseList(ListNode head){\n    ListNode last= null; \n    while(head!=null)\n    {\n        ListNode tmp=head.next; \n        head.next= last; \n        last=head;\n        head=tmp; \n    }\n        return last;\n    } \n    \n    \n    public ListNode addTwoNumbers(ListNode l1, ListNode l2) {\n         l1 = reverseList(l1);\n         l2 = reverseList(l2);\n        \n          ListNode head= null;\n\n          int carry=0;\n          while(l1!=null || l2!=null)\n          {\n              int sum=carry;\n        \n              if(l1!=null)\n                  sum+=l1.val;\n              \n              if(l2!=null)\n                 sum+= l2.val;\n                  \n              carry= sum/10;\n \n               ListNode curr = new ListNode(sum%10);\n               curr.next = head;\n               head = curr;\n              if(l1!=null) l1=l1.next;\n      \n              if(l2!=null)  l2=l2.next;\n   \n          }\n        if(carry>0)\n           {\n         ListNode curr = new ListNode(carry);\n            curr.next = head;\n            head = curr;\n        }\n       \n        return head;\n        \n    }\n}","compare_result":"","title_slug":"add-two-numbers-ii"}
